gobblin.ingestion.google.webmaster

Interface UrlGrouper

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterator<org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.Triple<String,gobblin.ingestion.google.webmaster.GoogleWebmasterFilter.FilterOperator,UrlTrieNode>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    UrlTriePrefixGrouper

    public interface UrlGrouper
extends Iterator<org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.Triple<String,gobblin.ingestion.google.webmaster.GoogleWebmasterFilter.FilterOperator,UrlTrieNode>>
    Package the URL pages/nodes into groups given the group size while traversing the UrlTrie by utilizing a TrieIterator. If the current node is not a "leaf" node defined by the TrieIterator, then a "fake" group of size 1 will be created by only including this node. Iterating the groups with a Triple type return value: Triple.1 is this group's root URL. The full URL to the root node of the group. Triple.2 is the FilterOperator type for this group. case 1. If the descendants of this group is <= groupSize, the operator is FilterOperator.CONTAINS. This is a real group. case 2. Otherwise, the node will only be returned if it exists, with the operator FilterOperator.EQUALS. This group is actually a single value. Triple.3 is the root node of this group.
